  "local_port": 57270,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What can I do with an infant at Walt Disney World?",
  "response": "Visiting Walt Disney World with an infant can be a magical experience, and there are plenty of activities and amenities designed to make your trip enjoyable for both you and your little one. Here are some things you can do:\n\n### Attractions and Rides\n1. **Gentle Rides**: Many attractions are suitable for infants. These include:\n   - **\"it's a small world\"** (Magic Kingdom)\n   - **Peter Pan's Flight** (Magic Kingdom)\n   - **The Many Adventures of Winnie the Pooh** (Magic Kingdom)\n   - **Living with the Land** (Epcot)\n   - **Na'vi River Journey** (Animal Kingdom)\n   \n2. **Character Meet and Greets**: Infants often enjoy seeing their favorite characters up close. Look for character meet-and-greet spots throughout the parks.\n\n### Baby Care Centers\nEach Disney park has a **Baby Care Center** equipped with nursing rooms, changing tables, feeding areas, and a kitchen with a microwave and sink. These centers also sell baby essentials like diapers, formula, and baby food.\n\n### Dining\n1. **High Chairs**: Most restaurants offer high chairs for infants.\n2. **Kid-Friendly Menus**: Many dining locations have options that are suitable for babies, such as mashed potatoes, mac and cheese, and fruit cups.\n3. **Baby Food**: You can bring your own baby food, or purchase it at the parks.\n\n### Stroller-Friendly Paths\nDisney parks are very stroller-friendly, with wide pathways and designated stroller parking areas near attractions and dining locations.\n\n### Shows and Parades\n1. **Festival of Fantasy Parade** (Magic Kingdom)\n2. **Mickey's Royal Friendship Faire** (Magic Kingdom)\n3. **Fantasmic!** (Hollywood Studios)\n4. **Rivers of Light** (Animal Kingdom)\n\nThese shows and parades are visually stimulating and can be enjoyable for infants.\n\n### Play Areas\n1. **Casey Jr. Splash 'N' Soak Station** (Magic Kingdom): A water play area where infants can splash around.\n2. **The Boneyard** (Animal Kingdom): A dinosaur-themed playground with a shaded dig site.\n\n### Relaxation Spots\n1. **Shaded Areas and Benches**: Take advantage of the many shaded areas and benches throughout the parks to rest and feed your baby.\n2. **Quiet Rides**: Rides like the **Tomorrowland Transit Authority PeopleMover** (Magic Kingdom) and **The Seas with Nemo & Friends** (Epcot) offer a calm, relaxing experience.\n\n### Rider Switch\nIf you have older children who want to go on rides that aren\u2019t suitable for infants, take advantage of Disney\u2019s **Rider Switch** service. One parent can wait with the infant while the other rides, then switch without waiting in line again.\n\n### Photo Opportunities\nCapture magical moments with your infant in front of iconic Disney landmarks, with characters, or during special events.\n\n### Special Touches\n1. **First Visit Button**: Pick up a \"My First Visit\" button at Guest Relations or your hotel to commemorate the occasion.\n2. **Memory Maker**: Consider purchasing the Memory Maker package to capture all your family photos taken by Disney photographers.\n\n### Stay Prepared\n1. **Pack Essentials**: Bring plenty of diapers, wipes, a change of clothes, and any other baby necessities.\n2. **Stay Hydrated**: Florida can be hot, so make sure both you and your baby stay hydrated.\n3. **Sun Protection**: Use stroller shades, hats, and baby-safe sunscreen to protect your infant from the sun.\n\nWith a little planning, your trip to Walt Disney World with an infant can be a wonderful experience for the whole family.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
